The paper deals with encoding algorithms for polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses memory and computation requirements, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper proposes a parallel encoding algorithm, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
